full_text: I suffer a lot, and every day the glass mirror get tougher to watch; I tie my stomach in knots.

I woke up this morning and figured I'd call you.
In case I'm not here tomorrow, I'm hoping that I can borrow a peace of mind, I'm behind on what's really important
My mind is really distorted, I find nothing but trouble in my life.
And I'm fresh as hell, Easter Day
I know the devil is real. I know the devil is real
